#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.234"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.234:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.234:0.2"
msgid "18. Samuddavagga"
msgstr "18. The Ocean"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.234:0.3"
msgid "234. Udāyīsutta"
msgstr "234. With Udāyī"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.234:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ca ānando āyasmā ca udāyī kosambiyaṃ viharanti "
"ghositārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the venerables Ānanda and Udāyī were staying near Kosambi, in "
"Ghosita’s Monastery."

msgctxt "sn35.234:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā udāyī sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā ānando "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Udāyī came out of retreat, went to "
"Venerable Ānanda, and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "sn35.234:1.3"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho āyasmā udāyī āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to Ānanda:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.234:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Yatheva nu kho, āvuso ānanda, ayaṃ kāyo bhagavatā anekapariyāyena akkhāto "
"vivaṭo pakāsito:"
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Ānanda, the Buddha has explained, opened, and illuminated in many "
"ways how this body is not-self."

msgctxt "sn35.234:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘itipāyaṃ kāyo anattā’ti, sakkā evameva viññāṇaṃ pidaṃ ācikkhituṃ desetuṃ "
"paññapetuṃ paṭṭhapetuṃ vivarituṃ vibhajituṃ uttānīkātuṃ: ‘itipidaṃ viññāṇaṃ "
"anattā’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Is it possible to explain consciousness in the same way? To teach, assert, "
"establish, open, analyze, and make it clear how consciousness is not-self?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.234:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Yatheva kho, āvuso udāyī, ayaṃ kāyo bhagavatā anekapariyāyena akkhāto "
"vivaṭo pakāsito:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.234:3.2"
msgid ""
"‘itipāyaṃ kāyo anattā’ti, sakkā evameva viññāṇaṃ pidaṃ ācikkhituṃ desetuṃ "
"paññapetuṃ paṭṭhapetuṃ vivarituṃ vibhajituṃ uttānīkātuṃ: ‘itipidaṃ viññāṇaṃ "
"anattā’”ti."
msgstr "“It is possible, Reverend Udāyī."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.167"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.234:4.1"
msgid "“Cakkhuñca, āvuso, paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇan”ti?"
msgstr "Does eye consciousness arise dependent on the eye and sights?”"

msgctxt "sn35.234:4.2"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti."
msgstr "“Yes, reverend.”"

msgctxt "sn35.234:4.3"
msgid ""
"“Yo cāvuso, hetu, yo ca paccayo cakkhuviññāṇassa uppādāya, so ca hetu, so ca "
"paccayo sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjheyya. Api nu kho "
"cakkhuviññāṇaṃ paññāyethā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“If the cause and condition that gives rise to eye consciousness were to "
"totally and utterly cease without anything left over, would eye "
"consciousness still be found?”"

msgctxt "sn35.234:4.4"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr "“No, reverend.”"

msgctxt "sn35.234:4.5"
msgid ""
"“Imināpi kho etaṃ, āvuso, pariyāyena bhagavatā akkhātaṃ vivaṭaṃ pakāsitaṃ: ‘"
"itipidaṃ viññāṇaṃ anattā’”ti … pe …."
msgstr "“In this way, too, it can be understood how consciousness is not-self."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.234:5.1"
msgid "“Jivhañcāvuso, paṭicca rase ca uppajjati jivhāviññāṇan”ti?"
msgstr "Does ear … nose … tongue … body …"

msgctxt "sn35.234:5.2"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.234:5.3"
msgid ""
"“Yo cāvuso, hetu yo ca paccayo jivhāviññāṇassa uppādāya, so ca hetu, so ca "
"paccayo sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjheyya, api nu kho "
"jivhāviññāṇaṃ paññāyethā”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.234:5.4"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.234:5.5"
msgid ""
"“Imināpi kho etaṃ, āvuso, pariyāyena bhagavatā akkhātaṃ vivaṭaṃ pakāsitaṃ: ‘"
"itipidaṃ viññāṇaṃ anattā’”ti … pe …."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.234:6.1"
msgid "“Manañcāvuso, paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati manoviññāṇan”ti?"
msgstr "mind consciousness arise dependent on the mind and thoughts?”"

msgctxt "sn35.234:6.2"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti."
msgstr "“Yes, reverend.”"

msgctxt "sn35.234:6.3"
msgid ""
"“Yo cāvuso, hetu, yo ca paccayo manoviññāṇassa uppādāya, so ca hetu, so ca "
"paccayo sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjheyya, api nu kho "
"manoviññāṇaṃ paññāyethā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“If the cause and condition that gives rise to mind consciousness were to "
"totally and utterly cease without anything left over, would mind "
"consciousness still be found?”"

msgctxt "sn35.234:6.4"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr "“No, reverend.”"

msgctxt "sn35.234:6.5"
msgid ""
"“Imināpi kho etaṃ, āvuso, pariyāyena bhagavatā akkhātaṃ vivaṭaṃ pakāsitaṃ: ‘"
"itipidaṃ viññāṇaṃ anattā’ti."
msgstr "“In this way, too, it can be understood how consciousness is not-self."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.168"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
#. VAR: akukkukajātaṃ → akukkuṭakajātaṃ (s1, s2, km) | akukkuṭakajātakaṃ (s3) | akukkajaṭajātaṃ (mr)
#. VAR: vinibbhujeyya → vinibbhajjeyya (s1-3, km) | vinibbhujjeyya (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.234:7.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, āvuso, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno "
"tiṇhaṃ kuṭhāriṃ ādāya vanaṃ paviseyya. So tattha passeyya mahantaṃ "
"kadalikkhandhaṃ ujuṃ navaṃ akukkukajātaṃ. Tamenaṃ mūle chindeyya; mūle "
"chetvā agge chindeyya; agge chetvā pattavaṭṭiṃ vinibbhujeyya. So tattha "
"pheggumpi nādhigaccheyya, kuto sāraṃ."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a person in need of heartwood. Wandering in search of "
"heartwood, they’d take a sharp axe and enter a forest. There they’d see a "
"big banana tree, straight and young and grown free of defects. They’d cut it "
"down at the base, cut off the root, cut off the top, and unroll the coiled "
"sheaths. But they wouldn’t even find sapwood, much less heartwood."

msgctxt "sn35.234:7.2"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, āvuso, bhikkhu chasu phassāyatanesu nevattānaṃ na attaniyaṃ "
"samanupassati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant sees these six fields of contact as neither "
"self nor belonging to self."

# BB adopts the negative form of asamanupassanto here. But in the previous sentence the negative was applied to the object, not the verb.
#. VAR: evaṃ asamanupassanto → evaṃ samanupassanto (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.234:7.3"
msgid "So evaṃ asamanupassanto na kiñci loke upādiyati. "
msgstr "So seeing, they don’t grasp anything in the world. "

msgctxt "sn35.234:7.4"
msgid "Anupādiyaṃ na paritassati. Aparitassaṃ paccattaññeva parinibbāyati."
msgstr ""
"Not grasping, they’re not anxious. Not being anxious, they personally become "
"extinguished."

msgctxt "sn35.234:7.5"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānātī”ti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been "
"completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any "
"state of existence.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.234:7.6"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
